Worldwide Advertising & Media Digest - July 15 . - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - WAM - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - . . . . REUTERS WORLDWIDE ADVERTISING & MEDIA DIGEST . . . . . - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - July 15 , 1997 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Reuters news from around the world on Advertising , Marketing , Media , the Internet , Brand - name Products and Consumer Trends * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * ADVERTISING & MARKETING : LONDON - All European Union states should ban tobacco advertising and move to limit smoking in any way they can , says Europe ' s social affairs commissioner Padraig Flynn . * * * * * * * * * FRANKFURT - The main association of German advertising agencies , GWA , says most of its members are satisfied with business in the first half of the year and predict further growth in the second half . * * * * * * * * * IRVING , Texas - Evergreen Media Corp and Chancellor Broadcasting Co say they have a definitive agreement to acquire Katz Media Group Inc for about $ 373 million . Katz sells national advertising time for radio stations , television stations , cable systems and Internet sites throughout the U . S . * * * * * * * * * LONDON - Virgin Group boss Richard Branson says his companies will sponsor sports that lose any funding from tobacco companies . " Even an international sport like the Grand Prix need not suffer , " he says . * * * * * * * * * NEW YORK - BNN Corp forms a unit with Interpublic Group of Cos Inc to handle sports and event marketing for General Motors Corp . * * * * * * * * * LONDON - Some 61 percent of Britons back a complete ban on tobacco advertising , an idea currently being considered by the government , according to a survey by the Office of National Statistics . * * * * * * * * * GREENWICH , Connecticut - NFO Research Inc . agrees to buy market research firm MBL Group Plc in a deal valued at $ 55 million . * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * MEDIA & THE INTERNET : HAMBURG - Italian fashion group Benetton is looking for a German publisher for its in - house - produced magazine Colors , marketing newsletter New Business reports . * * * * * * * * * LONDON - Business and industry magazine publisher Euromoney Publications Plc is expected to announce shortly that it is buying Institutional Investor from Walt Disney , the Guardian newspaper says . Euromoney is expected to pay up to $ 130 million for the specialist financial publications house . * * * * * * * * * CANBERRA - The Australian government says it will develop a national voluntary code aimed at regulating the content of on - line services , without restricting industry growth . * * * * * * * * * HAMBURG - The German weekly news magazine Der Spiegel and Deutsche Bahn railway company have started a daily newspaper for German rail travellers aimed at business readers on late - afternoon express trains . * * * * * * * * * NEW YORK - Time Warner Inc Chief Financial Officer Richard Bressler says the company doesn ' t expect to make any more significant acquisitions in the foreseeable future . * * * * * * * * * LOS ANGELES - The WB Television Network , owned by Time Warner Inc , says five stations affiliated with rival United Paramount Network have agreed to switch to The WB in January 1998 . * * * * * * * * * FRANKFURT - A week after their much - hyped launch following a frantic subscription period , shares in television network ProSieben Media AG have settled at a solid but modest premium to their issue price . * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * BRAND - NAME PRODUCTS & MARKETS : BRUSSELS - West European car sales soared nine percent year - on - year in June , partly reflecting a booming Italian market triggered by an incentive scheme , the European Automobile Manufacturers ' Association says . * * * * * * * * * TOKYO - Canon Inc says it has developed the world ' s first chip for digital video cameras . The new chip paves the way for the development of smaller , energy - saving , higher quality cameras which can be easily connected to personal computers and other multimedia equipment , Canon says . * * * * * * * * * SEOUL - Two years after South Korea agreed to take additional steps to open up its auto market , the country remains " very , very closed " to imports , the president of the American Automobile Manufacturers ' Association says . * * * * * * * * * UDINE , Italy - An Italian company says it will not take its " Fuehrer " wine off the market despite a storm of protest . The wine , which shows Nazi dictator Adolf Hitler on the label , comes in two types - - " Sieg Heil " ( Hail Victory ) and " Ein Volk , Ein Reich , Ein Fuehrer " ( One People , One Empire , One Leader ) . It also sells other wines named after Che Guevara , Lenin and Karl Marx . * * * * * * * * * TOKYO - Inchcape Peugeot Japan Co Ltd , the Japanese import and distribution unit for Peugeot cars , says it is aiming for Japanese sales of 20 , 000 cars in the year 2000 . * * * * * * * * * BEIJING - A corporate restructuring by China ' s Tsingtao Brewery Co Ltd is aimed at rebuilding the beer maker ' s image and will boost returns for investors , the China Daily says . * * * * * * * * * TOKYO - Sales of Bandai Co Ltd ' s " virtual pet " Tamagotchi are expected to reach 10 million , the business daily Nihon Keizai Shimbun reports . * * * * * * * * * BEIJING - China is to set up several large - scale chain store groups in the next five to 10 years in a bid to make its domestic retail sector more competitive , the People ' s Daily says . * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * CONSUMER TRENDS : KUALA LUMPUR - From the price of wheat to petrol , Southeast Asian consumers may begin feeling the pinch of rising interest rates , analysts say . * * * * * * * * * JERUSALEM - The sign outside the door reads " Coffee Shop , " but visitors at the cafe just inside Jerusalem ' s walled Old City get more than a cappuccino . Known in Christian circles as a cafe on the " cutting edge of modern - day evangelism , " and to Jews and Moslems as a place to avoid , the Loaves & Fishes Cafe employs young missionaries zealous about spreading the word . * * * * * * * * * HO CHI MINH CITY , Vietnam - Vietnamese architects have a solution for the city ' s overcrowding - - build satellite cities and move some 600 , 000 people into them . * * * * * * * * * ANGKOR WAT , Cambodia - A bloody coup and the onset of the rainy season have left Cambodia ' s magnificent 12th century ruins at Angkor Wat high and dry for tourists , say tourism officials . * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * - - London Advertising Newsdesk + 44 171 542 2792 * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * See full stories on Reuters Advertising & Media Briefing . And why not visit our Internet site athttp : / / www . bizinfo . reuters . com ? * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * 
